WEBVTT

00:01.710 --> 00:04.171
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:06.924 --> 00:08.091
[ Dog barking in distance ]

00:09.551 --> 00:11.512
Control, 7‐Adam‐15.

00:11.512 --> 00:13.889
We have a structure fire
at 8650 Magnolia.

00:13.889 --> 00:16.266
Please notify LAFD.

00:16.266 --> 00:17.309
You think
anyone's in there?

00:17.309 --> 00:18.519
Well, no one
that's supposed to be.

00:18.519 --> 00:20.187
Man: Help!
Was that a scream?

00:20.187 --> 00:22.189
♪♪

00:22.189 --> 00:23.857
Control, what's the ETA
on LAFD?

00:23.857 --> 00:25.359
Dispatch: Two minutes.

00:25.359 --> 00:26.735
That's ‐‐ That's
too long.

00:26.735 --> 00:27.861
Control, be advised,
we're going in

00:27.861 --> 00:29.529
to look for victims.

00:29.529 --> 00:31.156
♪ Pull me into
your coloring books ♪
Ready?

00:31.156 --> 00:33.492
♪ Lead me into
your bright adventures ♪

00:33.492 --> 00:37.579
♪♪

00:37.579 --> 00:39.540
♪ Kiss me under the mistletoe ♪
[ Glass shattering ]

00:39.540 --> 00:41.750
♪ Open‐mouth
on my brand‐new dentures ♪

00:41.750 --> 00:43.210
[ Debris crashing ]

00:43.210 --> 00:44.586
♪♪

00:44.586 --> 00:45.879
Geez.

00:45.879 --> 00:47.965
Man: Help me!
[ Coughs ]

00:47.965 --> 00:51.093
♪ Who met in the future
and moved to the past ♪

00:51.093 --> 00:54.304
Man: Help!
Someone help me!

00:54.304 --> 00:56.348
[ Coughing ]
♪ All big men
have a gravity ♪

00:56.348 --> 00:58.558
♪ That draws them
to the sun ♪

00:58.558 --> 01:01.061
♪ And gives them
their authority ♪

01:01.061 --> 01:03.230
♪ And gives them
their control ♪
[ Groans ]

01:03.230 --> 01:04.773
Whoa, man.

01:04.773 --> 01:07.442
♪ Gravity that draws them
to the sun ♪
[ Groans ]

01:07.442 --> 01:09.236
[ All coughing, panting ]

01:10.779 --> 01:13.490
[ Sirens wailing ]

01:13.490 --> 01:15.033
[ Glass shattering ]

01:15.033 --> 01:17.578
[ All coughing ]

01:17.578 --> 01:20.956
♪♪

01:20.956 --> 01:22.457
[ Coughing ]

01:22.457 --> 01:24.918
[ Indistinct chatter ]

01:24.918 --> 01:26.837
Is there
anyone else inside?

01:26.837 --> 01:28.672
Not that we saw.
You shouldn't have
gone in.

01:28.672 --> 01:30.591
Well, it's kind of
our job, saving people.

01:30.591 --> 01:31.675
From crime.

01:31.675 --> 01:33.760
You don't see us
running towards gunfire.

01:33.760 --> 01:35.887
You think that's just wood smoke
you're breathing in?

01:35.887 --> 01:38.015
All the toxic things in a home,
once they catch fire,

01:38.015 --> 01:40.017
they turn to deadly gases ‐‐

01:40.017 --> 01:42.936
ammonia, carbon dioxide,
hydrogen cyanide.

01:42.936 --> 01:45.564
So unless you want me
dragging your ass to safety

01:45.564 --> 01:47.065
in the future,
you'll leave the rescues

01:47.065 --> 01:49.568
to the professionals.

01:49.568 --> 01:50.777
[ Sighs ]

01:50.777 --> 01:52.487
[ Sirens wailing ]

01:54.656 --> 01:56.241
How's it going
with you two?
Really good.

01:56.241 --> 01:57.951
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh ♪
Really good.

01:57.951 --> 01:59.828
♪ Oh, oh, whoa, oh, oh ♪

01:59.828 --> 02:02.372
♪ I'm gonna win for you ♪

02:02.372 --> 02:04.833
♪ Like I know
you want me to do ♪
[ Sniffs ]

02:04.833 --> 02:06.126
How is it that
I still smell like smoke

02:06.126 --> 02:07.627
after a 30‐minute shower?

02:07.627 --> 02:08.837
Welcome to my world.

02:08.837 --> 02:10.255
You always smell
fantastic.

02:10.255 --> 02:12.424
That's because I spend
half my salary on perfumes,

02:12.424 --> 02:14.593
potions, and detergents.

02:14.593 --> 02:17.721
Well, it's working.
[ Chuckles ]

02:17.721 --> 02:20.223
Do you think
that fire was arson?

02:20.223 --> 02:22.351
Maybe.
I smelled accelerant.

02:22.351 --> 02:24.227
The arson investigator
will know for sure.

02:24.227 --> 02:25.937
You ever think
about doing that?

02:25.937 --> 02:27.439
Arson investigation?
Yeah.

02:27.439 --> 02:28.523
No.

02:28.523 --> 02:30.692
I like the physical part
of firefighting.

02:30.692 --> 02:32.861
Plus, I wouldn't have time
for all my extracurriculars ‐‐

02:32.861 --> 02:34.571
Army Reserve, teaching,

02:34.571 --> 02:35.739
motorcycle racing...

02:35.739 --> 02:37.491
Dating me.
Dating you.

02:37.491 --> 02:40.619
"Motorcycle racing"?
[ Cellphone vibrates, chimes ]

02:40.619 --> 02:42.120
What is it?

02:42.120 --> 02:44.289
[ Gasps ]
They found a body.

02:45.582 --> 02:47.501
[ Sirens wailing,
radio chatter ]

02:47.501 --> 02:50.045
Karl.
Hey, Bailey.

02:50.045 --> 02:51.880
This is John Nolan,
LAPD.

02:51.880 --> 02:53.382
Hey.
He and his partner
pulled the survivor out

02:53.382 --> 02:54.591
before we got here.
Ah.

02:54.591 --> 02:56.301
Did you give him the lecture
about how stupid it is

02:56.301 --> 02:58.178
to go into a structure fire
without a mask?

02:58.178 --> 03:00.013
It was given ‐‐
and understood.

03:00.013 --> 03:02.015
Any, uh, luck
ID'ing the victim yet?

03:02.015 --> 03:03.392
Nah, it's too soon.

03:03.392 --> 03:05.310
There were fifth‐
and sixth‐degree burns.

03:05.310 --> 03:07.688
But from the size,
I'd say it was a man.

03:07.688 --> 03:09.773
And you might want to start
referring to him

03:09.773 --> 03:12.109
as a suspect
instead of the victim.

03:12.109 --> 03:14.236
You think our DB
started the fire?

03:14.236 --> 03:15.987
That's what
the evidence suggests.

03:15.987 --> 03:17.364
He was right
where it started,

03:17.364 --> 03:19.157
and an accelerant
was definitely used.

03:19.157 --> 03:20.534
No way it could've been
just an addict

03:20.534 --> 03:21.785
falling asleep
next to a lit candle?

03:21.785 --> 03:24.079
No, no, no, no, that fire
got too hot, too fast.

03:24.079 --> 03:26.123
So, what are you thinking?

03:26.123 --> 03:27.666
That the guy
we pulled out of there

03:27.666 --> 03:30.168
might be able
to give us some insight.

03:30.168 --> 03:32.712
Wesley: [ Sighs ]
So, how's the book?

03:32.712 --> 03:34.506
Terrible, but who cares?

03:34.506 --> 03:36.258
It's my third
maternity‐leave book.

03:36.258 --> 03:38.969
I've been lucky to average
one a year up till now.
[ Baby coos ]

03:38.969 --> 03:40.929
Maybe I should
extend my leave,

03:40.929 --> 03:42.806
spend a little more time
with Jack.

03:42.806 --> 03:44.099
I think
that's a great idea.

03:44.099 --> 03:46.184
Because you don't want me
to go back to work?

03:46.184 --> 03:47.602
Because you want me to quit
being a detective

03:47.602 --> 03:49.104
and focus on
what really matters?
Uh ‐‐

03:49.104 --> 03:51.273
Because you think I won't
fulfill my mom potential

03:51.273 --> 03:52.983
if I'm at crime scenes
all day?

03:52.983 --> 03:54.443
Wow.

03:54.443 --> 03:55.527
Where did that
come from?

03:55.527 --> 03:57.070
I don't know.

03:58.780 --> 04:01.783
Clearly, I'm a little conflicted
about going back to work.

04:03.368 --> 04:06.329
I want you to do
whatever makes you happy.

04:06.329 --> 04:07.914
But I do think
that it's time

04:07.914 --> 04:10.834
to leave the baby home
for a night and go on a date.

04:10.834 --> 04:12.210
Who'll watch Jack?

04:12.210 --> 04:14.212
[ Stammers ]
Your mom, my mom,

04:14.212 --> 04:16.756
or some teenager
we pull off the street?

04:16.756 --> 04:18.175
Who cares?

04:18.175 --> 04:19.259
We deserve
some alone time.

04:19.259 --> 04:21.636
And some fine dining?
Hell, yes.

04:21.636 --> 04:23.138
The fancier, the better.
I'm in.

04:23.138 --> 04:24.806
[ Cellphone chimes ]

04:28.643 --> 04:30.896
♪♪

04:30.896 --> 04:33.857
Client. Um, I have
a meeting I forgot about.

04:33.857 --> 04:36.485
I'll make, uh, reservations
for 7:00, okay?

04:38.653 --> 04:41.156
Hey.

04:41.156 --> 04:43.033
I love you.
I love you, too.

04:43.033 --> 04:45.952
♪♪

04:48.288 --> 04:50.540
Hey, how's it going
with Harper?

04:50.540 --> 04:53.460
I mean, I'm still here,
so...good, I guess.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.796
She was my training officer.
You're in great hands.

04:55.796 --> 04:57.214
Look, I'm just trying to do
whatever I can to keep her

04:57.214 --> 04:58.590
from giving me that look.

04:58.590 --> 05:00.342
Oh, the Triple D?
Yeah, I know it well.

05:00.342 --> 05:03.720
Disappointment,
disbelief, and disdain.

05:03.720 --> 05:05.096
I think she developed it
in a lab somewhere

05:05.096 --> 05:06.765
to destroy self‐confidence.

05:06.765 --> 05:09.059
Yeah, my mom has
a version of it.

05:09.059 --> 05:11.186
You think I'd be immune given
how often she's used it on me

05:11.186 --> 05:12.687
over the years.

05:12.687 --> 05:14.481
Yeah, well, Harper uses it
on the daily ‐‐

05:14.481 --> 05:16.399
I'm still not used to it.
Hang in there.

05:16.399 --> 05:19.152
So, I also need you
to cover C Division today.

05:19.152 --> 05:20.362
Anything else you need?

05:20.362 --> 05:22.030
Paint your house
or clean your car?

05:22.030 --> 05:23.532
[ Chuckles ]

05:23.532 --> 05:26.326
I got two roving sergeants
for six divisions.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.745
Welcome to
your new reality.

05:28.745 --> 05:30.705
That's why you should take on
a sergeant's aide.

05:30.705 --> 05:33.333
[ Scoffs ]
I don't need an aide.

05:33.333 --> 05:35.710
It's not a sign
of weakness.

05:35.710 --> 05:39.297
It's a necessity given
how under‐resourced we are.

05:39.297 --> 05:41.216
Yeah, I guess I could use
a go‐fer.

05:41.216 --> 05:43.802
Someone to go‐fer coffee
or supplies.

05:43.802 --> 05:44.803
Call it whatever you want.

05:44.803 --> 05:46.388
Just pull an officer out
at roll call.

05:46.388 --> 05:48.682
[ Locker door closes ]
Hell, pull Chen.

05:48.682 --> 05:50.183
You two
work together good.

05:51.810 --> 05:54.813
Tim is going to ask you
to be his go‐fer.

05:54.813 --> 05:55.939
What? His ‐‐ His what?

05:55.939 --> 05:57.357
His aide.

05:57.357 --> 05:59.025
He's stretched a little thin.

05:59.025 --> 06:01.319
Grey suggested
he take you on to assist.

06:01.319 --> 06:02.988
Me specifically?
Yeah.

06:02.988 --> 06:05.699
Uh, is there a problem?

06:05.699 --> 06:07.117
No, ma'am.

06:07.117 --> 06:08.535
I'm just excited to hear
what new nicknames

06:08.535 --> 06:09.786
you came up with for me.

06:09.786 --> 06:11.371
Hm. Uh, I've ‐‐

06:11.371 --> 06:13.290
I've narrowed it down
to three.

06:13.290 --> 06:16.251
Um, "Get out
of my face"...
Mm‐hmm.

06:16.251 --> 06:18.128
..."sit your ass down"...
Okay.

06:18.128 --> 06:20.589
...and "I will tell you
when I am ready."

06:23.049 --> 06:25.051
I love them all.
Okay.

06:25.051 --> 06:26.803
Triple D.

06:26.803 --> 06:29.890
What was that?
Nothing.
Just sitting my ass down.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.808
Sgt. Grey: So, all right,
settle down, everyone.

06:31.808 --> 06:34.102
Sergeant Bradford,
you want to start us off?

06:34.102 --> 06:35.729
Yes. Um...

06:35.729 --> 06:37.188
I'm in need of a go‐fer.

06:37.188 --> 06:38.607
Now, it won't be glamorous,

06:38.607 --> 06:40.650
but it'll be
a learning experience.

06:40.650 --> 06:42.986
♪♪

06:42.986 --> 06:44.946
Webb, how about it?

06:44.946 --> 06:46.156
You ready
to get off patrol?

06:46.156 --> 06:48.116
Yes, sir.
Looking forward to it.

06:48.116 --> 06:49.492
You said ‐‐
I thought ‐‐

06:49.492 --> 06:52.120
Officer Nolan,
so I saw your request

06:52.120 --> 06:53.163
to follow up on the man
you pulled out

06:53.163 --> 06:54.623
of the fire yesterday.
Yes, sir.

06:54.623 --> 06:56.583
I checked with the hospital.
He regained consciousness.

06:56.583 --> 06:57.834
Thought it would be important
to get his statement

06:57.834 --> 06:59.252
while his memory was fresh.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.045
I agree.

07:00.045 --> 07:01.129
I'll notify Caradine

07:01.129 --> 07:02.922
for when he assigns
a detective.

07:04.299 --> 07:06.384
Harper:
You're driving today.

07:06.384 --> 07:07.802
Hey, you know
I almost qualified to race

07:07.802 --> 07:08.887
in the British
Grand Prix, right?

07:08.887 --> 07:10.930
I mean,
before my troubles.

07:10.930 --> 07:12.641
And you've never
known real fear

07:12.641 --> 07:14.726
until you've gone airborne
in a Formula 1 car.

07:14.726 --> 07:18.188
Yeah, try being hunted
by a pack of cartel sicarios,

07:18.188 --> 07:19.731
then get back to me.

07:19.731 --> 07:21.650
Okay, <i>that's</i> a story
I want to hear.

07:21.650 --> 07:22.984
Alonzo: Nyla.

07:22.984 --> 07:25.362
Harper: Hi.
[ Chuckles ]

07:25.362 --> 07:26.905
What are you
doing here?

07:26.905 --> 07:29.282
Just stopped by
to ask you to lunch.

07:29.282 --> 07:31.284
It's 9:00 A. M.

07:31.284 --> 07:33.036
Oh, right. Sorry.

07:33.036 --> 07:34.329
When your kid gets up
before the sun,

07:34.329 --> 07:36.039
you lose track of time.

07:36.039 --> 07:39.250
[ Inhales deeply ]
Uh, plus, I was wondering, um,

07:39.250 --> 07:41.628
if you could take care
of this ticket for me.

07:41.628 --> 07:44.381
Unh‐unh. No.
Put it away. I can't.

07:44.381 --> 07:46.966
I'm gonna go
set up the shop.
Mm‐hmm.

07:46.966 --> 07:49.094
Sorry. I knew
I shouldn't have asked.

07:49.094 --> 07:51.971
Yeah, you also shouldn't have
been going 60 in a 30.

07:51.971 --> 07:53.264
What were you thinking?

07:53.264 --> 07:54.808
That my ex was gonna
tear me a new one

07:54.808 --> 07:56.726
if I was late
for my pickup again.

07:56.726 --> 07:58.228
That's no excuse.

07:58.228 --> 08:00.772
Can I take you
to dinner this week?

08:00.772 --> 08:01.981
I'd love that.

08:01.981 --> 08:03.191
I would too.

08:06.277 --> 08:08.029
[ Chuckles ]

08:08.029 --> 08:08.988
Is that your boyfriend?

08:11.199 --> 08:12.909
No, I'm just curious
to know, um,

08:12.909 --> 08:15.704
if I gave off any signals

08:15.704 --> 08:17.747
that would make you
comfortable enough...
Uh‐huh.

08:17.747 --> 08:20.583
...to ask me
a personal question.

08:20.583 --> 08:22.377
No, the ‐‐ um,
there were none.

08:22.377 --> 08:24.045
Mm.
There were
no signals given.

08:24.045 --> 08:27.340
Um, that's what some people
like to call "my bad."

08:27.340 --> 08:30.009
Mm‐hmm. Get your ass
in the shop, Boot.
Okay.

08:30.009 --> 08:31.678
Why would you tell me that
Tim was going to pick me

08:31.678 --> 08:32.887
when he didn't?

08:32.887 --> 08:34.806
Because Grey told him to.
Then why didn't he?

08:34.806 --> 08:36.599
I don't know, but clearly,
it bothers you.

08:36.599 --> 08:38.601
No, I just ‐‐

08:38.601 --> 08:40.854
It would make
a good career opportunity.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.480
As a roving supervisor,

08:42.480 --> 08:44.524
Tim responds to all
the high‐profile cases.

08:44.524 --> 08:46.359
And being
right there with him

08:46.359 --> 08:48.278
would make me stand out
when promotion time comes.

08:48.278 --> 08:49.571
So tell him
you want the gig.

08:49.571 --> 08:51.531
Oh, he would
just love that ‐‐

08:51.531 --> 08:54.534
being in a position
to decide my fate <i>again.</i>

08:54.534 --> 08:57.203
No...he'll come around.

08:57.203 --> 08:58.955
I just have
to give it time.

08:58.955 --> 09:01.166
Because the one thing
I know for sure

09:01.166 --> 09:04.794
is that Tim is definitely
missing me right now.

09:04.794 --> 09:06.463
I can't believe
the ump made that call ‐‐

09:06.463 --> 09:07.672
and in the bottom
of the ninth!

09:07.672 --> 09:08.923
It was clearly foul.

09:08.923 --> 09:10.842
B‐‐ I know ‐‐
by like three feet!

09:10.842 --> 09:12.093
What's the point
of instant replay

09:12.093 --> 09:13.261
if you're not gonna
get it right?

09:13.261 --> 09:15.722
Hey, man, you're preaching
to the choir.

09:15.722 --> 09:17.223
Hey, you know
I get season tickets

09:17.223 --> 09:18.475
to the Dodgers
and the Angels,

09:18.475 --> 09:20.018
so if you ever want
to hit up a game,

09:20.018 --> 09:21.352
just let me know.

09:21.352 --> 09:22.604
I'll hook you up.
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

09:22.604 --> 09:24.147
Don't say that
if you don't mean it,

09:24.147 --> 09:25.440
'cause I will call.

09:25.440 --> 09:27.859
Hey, that's the least
a go‐fer could do.

09:27.859 --> 09:29.444
"Aide."

09:29.444 --> 09:30.236
My man.

09:31.613 --> 09:33.364
Hi, there.
Lewis: Hi.

09:33.364 --> 09:35.075
Mr. Hall,
do you remember us?

09:35.075 --> 09:36.910
We pulled you out
of the fire yesterday.

09:36.910 --> 09:38.578
What were you doing
in the house?

09:38.578 --> 09:42.332
Oh, well, uh,
I‐I've been squatting there.

09:42.332 --> 09:44.667
Yeah, it's a lot safer
than being on the streets.

09:44.667 --> 09:46.669
Oh, of course.
How long have you been there?

09:46.669 --> 09:48.421
Since I returned.

09:48.421 --> 09:49.422
From...?

09:49.422 --> 09:50.965
Kremulus.

09:50.965 --> 09:52.592
And Kremulus is...?

09:52.592 --> 09:55.261
Oh, it's the planet right next
to Proxima Centauri,

09:55.261 --> 09:57.430
but no one really
knows about it,

09:57.430 --> 09:59.641
so please just keep it
to yourself.

09:59.641 --> 10:01.935
Oh, I‐I‐I think you can
count on us.
Mm‐hmm.

10:01.935 --> 10:03.478
Now, w‐were you there alone?

10:03.478 --> 10:05.188
Did anybody come back
with you?

10:05.188 --> 10:06.481
No.

10:06.481 --> 10:08.900
No, those who walk
a celestial path

10:08.900 --> 10:11.152
are destined for solitude.

10:12.320 --> 10:14.614
But I did hear
some voices yesterday.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.825
[ Softly ]
Okay, how do I put this?

10:16.825 --> 10:19.244
Were the voices...

10:19.244 --> 10:21.538
inside your head,
or were they ‐‐

10:21.538 --> 10:23.748
I‐I‐In the house.
Ah.

10:23.748 --> 10:25.500
Two guys.

10:25.500 --> 10:27.794
I‐I heard them come in
through the back.

10:27.794 --> 10:30.630
I hid so that
they wouldn't see me.

10:30.630 --> 10:34.592
And maybe...
half an hour later,

10:34.592 --> 10:36.136
that's when
the fire started.

10:37.470 --> 10:39.347
Did you hear
what the voices were saying?

10:39.347 --> 10:41.724
Would you recognize them
if you heard them again?

10:41.724 --> 10:43.184
No, they were
pretty muffled.

10:43.184 --> 10:45.478
And you're sure it wasn't
just one man?

10:45.478 --> 10:47.313
Yes...

10:47.313 --> 10:50.358
because one of them
was yelling...

10:51.776 --> 10:53.570
...and the other
was crying.

10:57.448 --> 11:00.577
Mr. Stone insisted
on waiting in your office.

11:00.577 --> 11:01.995
Of course he did.

11:01.995 --> 11:03.454
He's got a couple
shooters with him.

11:03.454 --> 11:05.206
Serious‐looking dudes.

11:05.206 --> 11:07.208
Feels like
a "car theft" situation.

11:07.208 --> 11:09.127
That's a good idea.

11:09.127 --> 11:10.587
All right,
give me two minutes.

11:13.548 --> 11:14.924
[ Sighs ]

11:14.924 --> 11:16.009
Hmm.

11:18.720 --> 11:20.388
Hey.

11:20.388 --> 11:21.723
Counselor.

11:21.723 --> 11:26.644
Punctuality is a quality
I expect from all my employees.

11:26.644 --> 11:28.188
Well, having a newborn

11:28.188 --> 11:30.690
kind of throws punctuality
out the window.

11:30.690 --> 11:33.568
Need I remind you why
you still have a son to dote on?

11:33.568 --> 11:35.570
No, I'm aware
of what I owe you.

11:35.570 --> 11:37.864
And yet, you spent
the last month

11:37.864 --> 11:40.700
on paternity leave,
avoiding paying me back,

11:40.700 --> 11:42.285
which makes me think

11:42.285 --> 11:44.162
you're trying to go back
on our deal.

11:44.162 --> 11:46.331
No, not at all.

11:46.331 --> 11:48.291
I just think that
I'm best used

11:48.291 --> 11:50.877
in an un‐muddied capacity.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.420
I have been meaning
to speak to you.

11:52.420 --> 11:54.339
I have a sterling reputation
with law enforcement,

11:54.339 --> 11:55.465
but that only benefits you
if I can continue ‐‐

11:55.465 --> 11:56.841
Shut up.

11:58.384 --> 12:01.304
You seem confused about
the dynamics at play here.

12:01.304 --> 12:03.932
You work for me now,
which means what I say goes ‐‐

12:03.932 --> 12:05.558
So sorry to interrupt,

12:05.558 --> 12:08.102
but someone just tried
to steal my car from out front.

12:08.102 --> 12:09.312
The police will be here
in a minute.

12:09.312 --> 12:10.897
Is that so?

12:10.897 --> 12:13.316
♪♪

12:13.316 --> 12:16.527
You know, the only thing
worse than stealing...

12:16.527 --> 12:18.112
in my book...

12:18.112 --> 12:19.489
is lying.

12:19.489 --> 12:22.283
[ Chuckles ]

12:22.283 --> 12:24.077
And yet, you lie
and steal for a living.

12:25.536 --> 12:27.705
What can I say?

12:27.705 --> 12:29.290
I'm a walking contradiction.

12:29.290 --> 12:34.295
♪♪

12:34.295 --> 12:37.048
Just think about
what we just spoke on.

12:37.048 --> 12:38.216
It'd be better
for everybody

12:38.216 --> 12:40.551
if I didn't have
to say it again.

12:40.551 --> 12:47.892
♪♪

12:50.728 --> 12:53.106
Harper: Where are we
right now, Boot?

12:53.106 --> 12:54.983
Uh, San Vicente and ‐‐

12:54.983 --> 12:56.401
If you have to look,
you don't know,

12:56.401 --> 12:58.653
and trouble is not gonna wait
for you to find a street sign.

12:58.653 --> 13:00.029
Got it. Sorry.

13:00.029 --> 13:01.781
I will do better.
[ Radio chatter ]

13:01.781 --> 13:03.491
[ Cellphone ringing ]

13:03.491 --> 13:04.284
You mind
if I take this?

13:06.119 --> 13:08.705
Whatever you think
is best.

13:08.705 --> 13:10.540
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Go for Aaron.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.583
Quinn: <i>Hey, Aaron,</i>
<i>it's Quinn from "TMZ."</i>

13:12.583 --> 13:13.918
<i>I really need</i>
<i>to talk to you.</i>

13:13.918 --> 13:15.878
Disguising your number.
Smart.

13:15.878 --> 13:17.297
Look, man, I told you
I'm not interested.
[ Monitor beeps ]

13:17.297 --> 13:19.382
An alert just came in.
You should check the box.

13:19.382 --> 13:20.425
<i>I've been calling you</i>
<i>all week, man.</i>

13:20.425 --> 13:21.592
<i>I can never reach you.</i>

13:21.592 --> 13:22.885
"Hollywood Division
is running a 246."

13:22.885 --> 13:25.096
<i>Look, hear me out</i>
<i>before you say no, okay?</i>

13:25.096 --> 13:26.806
"Drive‐by shooting
into a..."
<i>I've got a really sweet</i>
<i>deal for you.</i>

13:26.806 --> 13:29.851
<i>I've got my editor</i>
<i>to up the price to 100 grand.</i>

13:29.851 --> 13:31.728
Hey, look, man, I told you
I'm not interested, okay?

13:31.728 --> 13:32.937
Don't call me again.

13:32.937 --> 13:34.397
Uh, did you see the guy
in the trench coat?

13:34.397 --> 13:36.566
He might be
concealing a weapon.

13:36.566 --> 13:39.068
Dispatch: <i>7‐Adam‐19,</i>
<i>clear for traffic?</i>

13:39.068 --> 13:40.695
I didn't see a guy
in a trench coat.

13:40.695 --> 13:42.321
Should I turn around?
Do you think you should
turn around?

13:42.321 --> 13:43.781
I mean, did you see
a weapon?

13:43.781 --> 13:45.158
Did I say I saw one?

13:45.158 --> 13:47.118
<i>7‐Adam‐19?</i>
<i>Security check.</i>

13:47.118 --> 13:50.371
What was the drive‐by shooting
vehicle Hollywood was working?

13:50.371 --> 13:51.789
I‐I didn't s‐‐
It came over the radio.

13:53.249 --> 13:55.626
Right. Um, I was ‐‐

13:55.626 --> 13:57.712
I was looking for that guy
possibly concealing a weapon,

13:57.712 --> 13:59.297
but I will find him.

13:59.297 --> 14:02.216
Suspect's vehicle is a...

14:02.216 --> 14:04.302
<i>All units,</i>
<i>unable to raise 7‐Adam‐19.</i>

14:04.302 --> 14:06.721
<i>Last location near Stoner Park.</i>

14:06.721 --> 14:09.015
<i>7‐Adam‐100,</i>
<i>copy missing officer?</i>

14:09.015 --> 14:10.600
Oh, my God.
An officer's missing?

14:10.600 --> 14:12.143
Two.

14:12.143 --> 14:13.686
Two officers are missing.

14:13.686 --> 14:15.063
Okay, that's even worse!

14:15.063 --> 14:16.397
Should we look for them,

14:16.397 --> 14:18.149
or should we find
this trench‐coat guy?

14:18.149 --> 14:20.568
Tim: <i>7‐Adam‐100,</i>
<i>I copy the missing officer.</i>

14:20.568 --> 14:23.071
<i>Harper, it's Bradford.</i>
<i>You guys Code 4?</i>

14:23.071 --> 14:24.405
Code 4.

14:24.405 --> 14:25.782
What's our call sign?

14:26.991 --> 14:28.659
7‐Adam‐19.

14:29.994 --> 14:31.954
Ohhhh.

14:31.954 --> 14:33.998
We're the missing officers.
Mm.

14:33.998 --> 14:35.500
[ Clicks tongue ]
That is embarrassing.

14:35.500 --> 14:37.335
Yes, it is ‐‐ for you.

14:37.335 --> 14:38.753
I get a free pass
your first week.

14:38.753 --> 14:42.381
All of your many failures
are blamed on the Academy.

14:42.381 --> 14:45.093
So, what have you learned?

14:45.093 --> 14:47.512
That taking the wheel
is demanding enough...

14:47.512 --> 14:49.764
Mm‐hmm.
...and I shouldn't be
adding in

14:49.764 --> 14:51.474
personal phone calls
into the mix.

14:51.474 --> 14:52.892
Mm.

14:54.685 --> 14:57.021
There wasn't an armed man
in a trench coat, was there?

14:57.021 --> 14:58.356
Mm, mnh‐mnh.

15:01.234 --> 15:04.153
Hello! Didn't I see you guys
on a milk carton?

15:05.613 --> 15:07.865
I don't get it.

15:07.865 --> 15:09.826
'Cause we were
considered missing.

15:10.868 --> 15:13.204
They used to put pictures of
missing kids on milk cartons.

15:13.204 --> 15:15.373
Yes, in the '80s.
Yes, in the '80s.

15:15.373 --> 15:16.916
How did I end up
the punch line?
[ Laughs ]

15:16.916 --> 15:18.668
Oh, excuse me.
Uh, yeah.

15:18.668 --> 15:20.169
Harper: Hey, how come
Bradford didn't choose Lucy

15:20.169 --> 15:21.295
to be his go‐fer?

15:21.295 --> 15:22.880
I don't know,
but she's not being

15:22.880 --> 15:24.799
very adult about it.
Oh.

15:24.799 --> 15:27.468
So, how is it
riding with Tim?

15:27.468 --> 15:29.011
Oh, it's been great.

15:29.011 --> 15:30.054
You know, everyone
always talks about

15:30.054 --> 15:31.222
how tough
the Sarge can be,

15:31.222 --> 15:33.266
but we've been
having the best time.

15:33.266 --> 15:34.350
Really?

15:34.350 --> 15:36.227
That's...awesome.

15:36.227 --> 15:39.313
So, you know, when I was
riding with him,

15:39.313 --> 15:42.150
I learned some foolproof ways
to stay on his good side.

15:42.150 --> 15:44.277
You know, if you ‐‐ if ‐‐
if you want some tips.

15:44.277 --> 15:45.862
Yeah, that'd be great.

15:45.862 --> 15:47.196
Appreciate that.
[ Gunfire ]

15:47.196 --> 15:48.823
[ Car horn honks,
tires squealing ]

15:48.823 --> 15:50.491
Man: Look out!
Woman: [ Screams ] Hey!

15:50.491 --> 15:51.742
[ Indistinct shouting ]

15:51.742 --> 15:53.202
[ Tires screech ]

15:54.370 --> 15:55.913
Harper:
Let me see your hands!

15:55.913 --> 15:57.456
Show me your hands!
Guns down!
Get out of the car!

15:57.456 --> 15:58.916
Harper: Get out of the car!
Let me see your hands!

15:58.916 --> 16:01.544
Put your guns down!
Kip: Private security!
We got CCW permits!

16:01.544 --> 16:04.005
Someone just shot our client
through the windshield!

16:04.005 --> 16:05.339
Nolan:
Front seat clear!

16:05.339 --> 16:07.884
[ Indistinct shouting ]

16:07.884 --> 16:09.302
Man: Is everybody okay?!

16:10.595 --> 16:12.180
Sarge?
Tim: Yeah?

16:12.180 --> 16:14.015
I think we got a sniper.

16:14.015 --> 16:15.641
What do you see?

16:15.641 --> 16:17.643
Three shots grouped tight
high on the windshield.

16:17.643 --> 16:20.730
Judging from where the car was,
I'd say our sniper is northeast.

16:20.730 --> 16:22.064
Control, 7‐Adam‐100.

16:22.064 --> 16:23.232
We got a shooter
with a long gun

16:23.232 --> 16:24.901
at the 16000 block
of Rochester Avenue.

16:24.901 --> 16:26.652
I need eastbound traffic
from Veteran shut down.

16:26.652 --> 16:28.279
Get SWAT en route.

16:28.279 --> 16:30.281
Harper, Thorsen,
secure the scene.

16:30.281 --> 16:31.616
Nolan, Chen, Webb,
you're on me.

16:31.616 --> 16:32.909
Clear the street!
Move, move!

16:32.909 --> 16:35.119
Active shooter!
There's a shooter! Move, move!

16:35.119 --> 16:36.954
Get inside! Go!
There's a shooter!

16:36.954 --> 16:38.873
Get off the street!
Come on, move!

16:38.873 --> 16:41.250
[ Indistinct shouting ]

16:41.250 --> 16:44.170
♪ Looked the devil in the eye ♪
Hey!
Stop right there!

16:44.170 --> 16:45.755
♪ Taking risks is my design ♪

16:45.755 --> 16:47.423
♪ Y'all was born
without a spine ♪

16:47.423 --> 16:48.674
♪ Wicked and twisted ♪

16:48.674 --> 16:50.760
♪ Bars are sicker
than syphilis ♪

16:50.760 --> 16:52.303
♪ Spit and you listen ♪

16:52.303 --> 16:55.389
♪ Only way to stop,
I don't breathe again ♪

16:55.389 --> 16:56.641
♪ You wanna come around ♪
[ Gunshots ]

16:56.641 --> 16:58.059
♪ Yeah, see me then ♪

16:58.059 --> 17:03.481
♪♪

17:03.481 --> 17:04.690
7‐Adam‐15!

17:04.690 --> 17:06.776
Taking shots inside
16000 Rochester.

17:06.776 --> 17:09.111
Parking garage.
We're going up.

17:09.111 --> 17:11.072
Requesting more units
to cover the exits.

17:11.072 --> 17:16.911
♪♪

17:16.911 --> 17:18.871
♪ Go for broke
while you go for blows ♪

17:18.871 --> 17:20.706
♪ Jumping on the noose ♪
Tim: Get your hands up!

17:20.706 --> 17:23.668
♪♪

17:23.668 --> 17:26.170
♪ You wanna come around,
yeah, see me then ♪

17:26.170 --> 17:30.216
♪♪

17:30.216 --> 17:32.969
♪ You wanna come around,
yeah, see me then ♪

17:32.969 --> 17:35.096
♪♪

17:38.766 --> 17:41.477
[ Sighs ]

17:41.477 --> 17:43.813
I gotta admit, I'm disappointed
you didn't go after him.

17:43.813 --> 17:45.648
Oh, I was halfway
out the window.

17:45.648 --> 17:47.149
Lucy had to pull me back.

17:47.149 --> 17:49.026
Mm‐hmm.
Tim: This guy's
a pro, Sarge.

17:49.026 --> 17:50.987
Put three bullets
through tempered glass

17:50.987 --> 17:53.739
into a moving vehicle and still
dead‐centering his target ‐‐

17:53.739 --> 17:55.533
only a couple dozen people
in the world who could do that.

17:55.533 --> 17:58.244
The secondary escape route
screams elite training.

17:58.244 --> 18:00.705
Someone paid real money
for this guy's services.

18:00.705 --> 18:02.373
You got a name
on the target?
Michael Silver.

18:02.373 --> 18:04.041
Some kind of
import‐export guy.

18:04.041 --> 18:05.751
Hired a security company
a week ago.

18:05.751 --> 18:07.295
Didn't tell them why ‐‐

18:07.295 --> 18:08.629
or, at least,
they're not sharing with us.

18:08.629 --> 18:10.172
Intelligence unit
is running Silver's name

18:10.172 --> 18:12.216
to see if he's in
their database.

18:12.216 --> 18:14.427
Well, clearly, he pissed off
some bad people.

18:14.427 --> 18:16.762
Okay, we got an ID
on our arson victim.

18:16.762 --> 18:17.888
Nelson Crespo.

18:17.888 --> 18:19.265
He's a 35‐year‐old
restaurant manager,

18:19.265 --> 18:21.058
a couple of
minor drug arrests,

18:21.058 --> 18:22.643
and he has an apartment
in Culver City

18:22.643 --> 18:24.061
with his wife, Celia.

18:24.061 --> 18:25.855
Sir, we could handle
the death notification.

18:25.855 --> 18:27.356
See if Celia might
shed some light

18:27.356 --> 18:29.775
on what our DB was doing
in that house.

18:29.775 --> 18:31.235
All right, go ahead.

18:31.235 --> 18:34.155
I'll have Harper and Thorsen
work the sniper with Bradford.

18:34.155 --> 18:35.990
James: Nyla. Hey.

18:35.990 --> 18:37.116
James.
[ Laughter ]

18:37.116 --> 18:38.284
What are you
doing here?

18:38.284 --> 18:39.702
Oh, just picking up
a few things

18:39.702 --> 18:40.870
for the community center.

18:40.870 --> 18:43.873
I'd ask the same of you,
but I have a good guess.

18:43.873 --> 18:47.668
Yeah, I came for the coffee,
stayed for the sniper.

18:47.668 --> 18:50.588
Uh, this is my new rookie,
Officer Aaron ‐‐

18:50.588 --> 18:51.839
Thorsen.

18:51.839 --> 18:54.467
Yeah, I‐I remember
your case.

18:54.467 --> 18:56.510
Man, I‐I'm so sorry for
everything you went through.

18:56.510 --> 18:58.429
Thanks.
I happen to work with

18:58.429 --> 19:00.389
a lot of people who've been
wrongfully incarcerated.

19:00.389 --> 19:02.266
It can help to talk
to a therapist.

19:02.266 --> 19:03.726
I have some names
if you need 'em.

19:03.726 --> 19:06.687
I appreciate that,
but I already go twice a week.

19:06.687 --> 19:08.147
Good, good.

19:08.147 --> 19:09.899
Well, you are very lucky

19:09.899 --> 19:13.194
to have this impressive woman
as your training officer.

19:13.194 --> 19:14.403
Don't let her bite
scare you.

19:14.403 --> 19:15.571
She got a lot of heart.

19:15.571 --> 19:17.782
Uh, now, why would you
go and tell him that?

19:17.782 --> 19:19.867
Just to make your job
that much harder.
Huh.

19:19.867 --> 19:22.370
Uh, we are going out
again soon, right?

19:22.370 --> 19:23.704
You know it.

19:23.704 --> 19:26.582
All right, okay.

19:26.582 --> 19:27.917
Take care of yourself.

19:27.917 --> 19:29.085
[ Chuckles ]

19:31.921 --> 19:33.798
What?
Nothing.

19:33.798 --> 19:35.007
Good.

19:36.342 --> 19:37.968
Triple D's got game.

19:37.968 --> 19:39.512
You n‐‐
[ Clears throat ]

19:39.512 --> 19:41.472
It doesn't make sense.

19:41.472 --> 19:43.432
Nelson went for a jog
to the beach.

19:43.432 --> 19:45.518
What was he doing
near Griffith Park?

19:45.518 --> 19:46.769
H‐How'd he even get there?

19:46.769 --> 19:48.854
There's evidence that
the house he was found in

19:48.854 --> 19:50.606
is a place people go
to use drugs.

19:50.606 --> 19:51.857
No.

19:51.857 --> 19:55.152
Nelson was clean ‐‐
four years.

19:55.152 --> 19:58.197
Addicts relapse, uh, and ‐‐
and they lie about it.

19:58.197 --> 20:00.574
I know. I am one.

20:00.574 --> 20:02.576
If my husband
was using again,

20:02.576 --> 20:04.578
I would've seen the signs.

20:04.578 --> 20:06.497
Something happened
to him.

20:06.497 --> 20:10.292
Promise me you won't
just play "blame the addict."

20:10.292 --> 20:13.921
I promise you ‐‐ we will
follow this case where it leads.

20:15.506 --> 20:17.216
If you can think
of anything else,

20:17.216 --> 20:19.427
please call us ‐‐
day or night.

20:19.427 --> 20:22.179
And, again, I am truly sorry
for your loss.

20:22.179 --> 20:23.305
[ Breathing shakily ]

20:27.685 --> 20:29.145
You think
she's in denial?

20:29.145 --> 20:31.021
Maybe.

20:31.021 --> 20:32.940
Sure would be nice
to get some clarity.

20:32.940 --> 20:35.359
Well, hopefully,
the autopsy will give us that.

20:35.359 --> 20:36.777
All right,
thanks for checking.

20:36.777 --> 20:38.320
[ Radio chatter ]

20:38.320 --> 20:39.697
Intelligence's saying
that Michael Silver

20:39.697 --> 20:41.282
isn't on their radar.

20:41.282 --> 20:43.075
How's that possible?

20:43.075 --> 20:44.452
No way a guy
who gets popped

20:44.452 --> 20:46.162
by an elite sniper
is squeaky clean.

20:46.162 --> 20:49.206
He's gotta have some
criminal connection.
I'm gonna call Records.

20:49.206 --> 20:50.166
Maybe they have some
information, some ‐‐

20:50.166 --> 20:51.584
No, it's ‐‐ it's
a waste of time.

20:51.584 --> 20:53.544
I'll call LA CLEAR when
we get back to the station.

20:53.544 --> 20:55.463
Right.
[ Radio chatter ]

20:55.463 --> 20:58.591
[ Exhales slowly ]
Weird case, huh?

20:58.591 --> 20:59.842
Oh, yeah.

21:01.177 --> 21:03.304
I'm good with weird.

21:03.304 --> 21:04.722
I'm a Manx.

21:06.515 --> 21:07.516
I'm sorry.

21:07.516 --> 21:08.684
You're ‐‐ You're a what?

21:08.684 --> 21:10.060
A Manx.

21:10.060 --> 21:11.937
A Manx cat.

21:11.937 --> 21:13.522
That's my feline breed.

21:13.522 --> 21:15.691
My cat personality.

21:15.691 --> 21:17.818
What's your cat
personality, Sarge?

21:17.818 --> 21:20.029
Did Chen put you
up to this?

21:20.029 --> 21:21.155
Put me up to what?

21:21.155 --> 21:23.616
♪♪

21:23.616 --> 21:24.909
Whoa.
[ Saw whirring ]

21:24.909 --> 21:26.410
Oh, what, the smell?

21:26.410 --> 21:27.661
Yeah, it smells like
month‐old eggs

21:27.661 --> 21:29.455
and maggot meat.

21:29.455 --> 21:31.957
I mean, you don't ‐‐
you don't have to go in,

21:31.957 --> 21:34.710
but this is part
of the job.

21:34.710 --> 21:36.212
No, I'm good.
[ Clears throat ]
Mm.

21:36.212 --> 21:37.880
Can I just have a sec?
Oh, yeah, no.

21:37.880 --> 21:40.174
Gather yourself,
because what awaits

21:40.174 --> 21:43.260
smells like a septic tank
filled with tumors.

21:43.260 --> 21:46.639
[ Sniffs ] Okay...
I see what you're doing.

21:46.639 --> 21:48.891
This is payback for me trying
to get too familiar earlier,

21:48.891 --> 21:50.309
but you know what?

21:50.309 --> 21:52.853
It's all good.
I can handle it.

21:52.853 --> 21:54.355
I'm just gonna have
to cancel my reservation

21:54.355 --> 21:55.689
at Eliza and Elektra
tonight,

21:55.689 --> 21:58.025
because there's no way
I'm eating after this.

21:58.025 --> 21:59.777
Whoa, are you crazy?
You have to book that place

21:59.777 --> 22:01.821
like six months in advance.

22:01.821 --> 22:04.532
I dream of eating there.

22:04.532 --> 22:06.575
You want the reservation?

22:06.575 --> 22:07.701
Seriously?

22:07.701 --> 22:09.912
Yeah, it's yours ‐‐

22:09.912 --> 22:12.081
if you stop torturing me?

22:12.081 --> 22:13.165
Deal.

22:13.165 --> 22:15.042
Yeah.

22:15.042 --> 22:16.752
I mean,
the only question is,

22:16.752 --> 22:18.671
which boy toy
are you taking?

22:18.671 --> 22:20.548
Is it gonna be
the speed demon
from this morning,

22:20.548 --> 22:22.967
or the upright citizen
from this afternoon?

22:24.093 --> 22:25.386
I mean, unless
there's a third choice.

22:25.386 --> 22:26.887
No, it's James.

22:26.887 --> 22:29.265
It's definitely James.
But he's probably busy.

22:30.599 --> 22:32.184
Well, text him
and find out.

22:33.143 --> 22:34.144
[ Stammers ]

22:35.688 --> 22:37.147
[ Sighs ]
All right, fine.

22:38.983 --> 22:42.027
[ Cellphone buttons tapping ]

22:42.027 --> 22:43.070
[ Cellphone chimes ]

22:50.369 --> 22:51.871
Oh, no.

22:51.871 --> 22:55.583
The vanishing three dots.
That is the worst.

22:55.583 --> 22:58.252
He's probably gonna
respond later.

22:58.252 --> 22:59.420
You kn‐‐ Let's get
back to work.

22:59.420 --> 23:01.839
Right. [ Coughs ]

23:01.839 --> 23:03.549
[ Machine beeps,
tools whirring ]

23:05.551 --> 23:06.719
Detective.

23:06.719 --> 23:08.679
Nice to see you.

23:08.679 --> 23:11.098
Judging by the long sleeves
and queasy demeanor,

23:11.098 --> 23:12.641
I'd say you have
a new rookie.

23:12.641 --> 23:16.520
Yeah. Dr. Lowell,
meet Officer Thorsen.

23:16.520 --> 23:18.981
Of course.
Now I recognize you.

23:18.981 --> 23:21.358
You know, I have to say
that the forensic work

23:21.358 --> 23:23.444
in your case
seemed pretty solid.

23:23.444 --> 23:25.154
You're lucky the Parisians
set you free.

23:25.154 --> 23:27.573
I'm lucky the appeals court
understood that forensic science

23:27.573 --> 23:30.200
can be as corrupt
as the rest of law enforcement.

23:33.120 --> 23:34.538
First autopsy?

23:34.538 --> 23:35.539
Yeah.

23:35.539 --> 23:37.249
Smear this
under your nose.

23:37.249 --> 23:38.834
It'll help
with the smell.

23:38.834 --> 23:40.377
I'm surprised your TO
didn't tell you.

23:40.377 --> 23:42.129
I can't give away
all my secrets

23:42.129 --> 23:44.506
in the first week, Doc.

23:44.506 --> 23:47.426
So, you get anything useful
from the autopsy?

23:47.426 --> 23:50.846
Yeah, I found this
lodged in his T4 vertebra.

23:50.846 --> 23:53.098
Looks like
it's from a .223.

23:54.725 --> 23:57.603
Yeah, possible 77‐grain.

23:57.603 --> 24:00.940
Also known as NATO rounds
for their full metal jackets.

24:00.940 --> 24:02.983
Yeah, very heavy
and very lethal

24:02.983 --> 24:05.444
in a skilled marksman's hands.

24:05.444 --> 24:09.239
Yeah, to make a long‐distance
shot from a .223 round

24:09.239 --> 24:10.866
would require
a specialized weapon,

24:10.866 --> 24:12.743
which would seem
to confirm

24:12.743 --> 24:14.870
that our shooter
had military training.

24:14.870 --> 24:17.206
Nolan: Oh, hey.

24:17.206 --> 24:18.374
Wait a minute.

24:18.374 --> 24:20.292
She gave you the menthol
on your first visit?

24:20.292 --> 24:21.752
No, the ‐‐ the doc did.

24:21.752 --> 24:23.671
Ah, that makes sense.
[ Clears throat ]

24:23.671 --> 24:25.214
Harper: All right,
he's all yours.

24:25.214 --> 24:27.007
Let's go get you
a ginger ale.

24:27.007 --> 24:28.634
And you're here for...?

24:28.634 --> 24:29.677
Uh, Nelson Crespo.

24:29.677 --> 24:31.261
Ah, yes.
The burn victim.

24:31.261 --> 24:32.930
You know, you keep running
into conflagrations

24:32.930 --> 24:34.390
without oxygen masks,

24:34.390 --> 24:35.599
and you'll end up
in one of my drawers.

24:35.599 --> 24:36.892
Yeah, we've been told.

24:36.892 --> 24:39.228
So, you got anything
on Crespo?

24:39.228 --> 24:41.480
Well, I'm still writing up
my preliminary findings,

24:41.480 --> 24:44.692
but I did see something
unexpected in his x‐rays.

24:44.692 --> 24:47.319
He had a transverse fracture
to his left femur

24:47.319 --> 24:49.405
and compound fractures
to his pelvis.

24:49.405 --> 24:51.407
From when the ceiling
fell in on him?

24:51.407 --> 24:54.618
No. Actually, the fractures
were perimortem.

24:54.618 --> 24:56.537
Likely occurred an hour
before his death.

24:56.537 --> 24:57.705
That doesn't make
any sense.

24:57.705 --> 24:59.415
He would have been
in agony.

24:59.415 --> 25:01.083
Mm. Would explain
why he got caught

25:01.083 --> 25:02.042
in the fire he set.

25:02.042 --> 25:03.585
Oh, he didn't set it.

25:03.585 --> 25:05.295
There was no carbon monoxide
in his blood

25:05.295 --> 25:06.880
or soot in his lungs.

25:06.880 --> 25:09.091
Nelson Crespo was dead
before the fire even started.

25:13.929 --> 25:16.265
Hey, hope you and James
like the restaurant.

25:16.265 --> 25:17.433
Well, actually, he, uh ‐‐
he never replied,

25:17.433 --> 25:20.686
so it looks like I will be
going by myself.

25:20.686 --> 25:23.480
How about invite
the other guy, Alonzo?

25:23.480 --> 25:25.107
No.
Trust me.

25:25.107 --> 25:26.984
This ‐‐ This place
is romantic,

25:26.984 --> 25:28.819
and you're not gonna want
to eat there alone.

25:33.115 --> 25:35.075
Ooh, Harper.
Hey.

25:35.075 --> 25:36.368
Any leads on the sniper?
No.

25:36.368 --> 25:37.953
Uh, detectives are on it.

25:37.953 --> 25:39.872
Okay, when you catch him,

25:39.872 --> 25:41.290
ask him where
he gets his gear.

25:41.290 --> 25:43.167
What are you gonna do
with a zip line?

25:43.167 --> 25:45.085
You know how far it is
to my parking spot.

25:45.085 --> 25:46.295
[ Scoffs ]
[ Cellphone ringing ]

25:46.295 --> 25:48.297
Oh ‐‐ Angela.
Ask her about the baby.

25:48.297 --> 25:51.050
[ Chuckles ]
Hey. How's Jack?

25:51.050 --> 25:53.886
You can find out for yourself
if you come over and babysit.

25:53.886 --> 25:55.929
Both our moms bailed.

25:55.929 --> 25:57.431
It's for you.
[ Doorbell rings ]

25:58.849 --> 26:00.350
[ Indistinct chatter ]

26:00.350 --> 26:01.769
Thank you so much
for doing this.

26:01.769 --> 26:03.687
Of course.
It's our pleasure.
Yeah!

26:03.687 --> 26:06.190
Where is that
little rascal?

26:06.190 --> 26:07.483
Wesley's
putting him down.

26:07.483 --> 26:08.692
Mm.
Aw, look at him.

26:08.692 --> 26:09.985
Aw.

26:09.985 --> 26:12.112
[ Sniffs ] Wait,
did you start smoking?

26:12.112 --> 26:13.238
You can't smoke
around the baby.

26:13.238 --> 26:14.573
Uh, n‐‐ Please.
Come on.

26:14.573 --> 26:16.700
I ‐‐ No, I‐I walked
into a house fire yesterday

26:16.700 --> 26:18.827
instead of waiting
for the fire department...

26:18.827 --> 26:20.412
Mm‐hmm.
...which is what
I should have done.

26:20.412 --> 26:21.872
Mm‐hmm.

26:21.872 --> 26:24.875
It's turning into quite an
interesting case, actually.

26:24.875 --> 26:26.043
At first,
we thought the guy

26:26.043 --> 26:27.586
who started the fire
died in it,

26:27.586 --> 26:30.881
but the autopsy shows
he was dead before it started.

26:30.881 --> 26:31.965
Yeah,
with a crushed pelvis.

26:31.965 --> 26:33.801
No one knows
how he got it or where.

26:33.801 --> 26:35.135
Any witnesses?

26:35.135 --> 26:37.679
A transient with
clear mental‐health issues

26:37.679 --> 26:38.931
that we pulled out
of the house.

26:38.931 --> 26:40.849
He said he heard voices
before the fire started.

26:40.849 --> 26:42.434
Heard voices
or "heard voices"?

26:42.434 --> 26:44.186
That's what we said,
but given the condition

26:44.186 --> 26:46.146
our victim was in
before he died,

26:46.146 --> 26:48.023
I think our transient
actually heard our killer.

26:48.023 --> 26:49.274
Wesley: Okay,
baby's asleep.

26:49.274 --> 26:50.651
Let's go before
he realizes we're gone.

26:50.651 --> 26:51.652
Hi.
Hi.

26:51.652 --> 26:52.820
Bye.
Later.

26:54.780 --> 26:56.782
Don't call us.
Uh, of course.

26:56.782 --> 26:58.659
All right.

26:58.659 --> 26:59.952
So...
[ Laughs ]

26:59.952 --> 27:01.829
...what shall we do first?

27:01.829 --> 27:03.914
Order food, or...

27:05.207 --> 27:06.667
...make out?

27:06.667 --> 27:09.169
Order first and make out
while we wait.

27:09.169 --> 27:10.963
See, that's what I like
about you.

27:10.963 --> 27:12.381
You're always thinking.

27:12.381 --> 27:13.549
<i>That's</i> what you like
about me?

27:13.549 --> 27:15.134
Well, there's more,
and I could show you,

27:15.134 --> 27:16.135
but I'm on a schedule
right now.

27:16.135 --> 27:17.219
I have to order dinner.

27:17.219 --> 27:19.638
How dare you play
hard‐to‐get?

27:19.638 --> 27:21.515
Lopez: Ooh, and the sweet corn
fried rice.

27:21.515 --> 27:22.891
Hell, yeah.

27:22.891 --> 27:24.393
And, uh, meatballs?

27:24.393 --> 27:25.352
Ooh, two orders.

27:25.352 --> 27:27.020
And ‐‐ Ooh!

27:27.020 --> 27:28.272
The beet salad.

27:29.523 --> 27:30.566
Thanks.

27:31.608 --> 27:33.026
This is nice.

27:33.026 --> 27:34.695
This is amazing.
Mm.

27:34.695 --> 27:36.446
Mm.

27:36.446 --> 27:37.823
Ahh.
Mmm.

27:37.823 --> 27:40.200
Did you hear Nolan talking
about his murder case?

27:40.200 --> 27:43.996
It sounded challenging,
in an interesting way.

27:43.996 --> 27:46.456
Mm‐hmm.
What? It does.

27:46.456 --> 27:48.333
Angela, this is our
first date in months.

27:48.333 --> 27:50.127
I know, but what's more fun
than dinner and a murder?

27:52.212 --> 27:53.505
Fine. No murder.
[ Laughs ]

27:53.505 --> 27:55.007
Is that Nyla?

27:56.508 --> 27:59.261
I guess that's why
she couldn't babysit.
Mm‐hmm.

27:59.261 --> 28:05.559
♪♪

28:05.559 --> 28:06.476
Oh, my God.

28:07.728 --> 28:10.731
Ooh, I think I'm
a little under‐dressed.

28:10.731 --> 28:12.316
Nah, man ‐‐ it's L. A.

28:12.316 --> 28:13.859
I've seen people
wear flip‐flops

28:13.859 --> 28:15.277
to Michelin‐star
restaurants.
[ Laughs ]

28:15.277 --> 28:17.237
No one even blinks.

28:17.237 --> 28:18.822
I'm actually
meeting someone.

28:18.822 --> 28:20.324
[ Gasps ] Nyla.

28:20.324 --> 28:21.408
[ Laughs ]
Hey.

28:21.408 --> 28:23.076
You know her?

28:23.076 --> 28:24.953
She's my date.

28:24.953 --> 28:27.497
No, she's <i>my</i> date.

28:27.497 --> 28:29.625
[ Laughs ]
Uh, actually...

28:29.625 --> 28:32.628
y‐you are both my dates.

28:32.628 --> 28:34.171
[ Chuckles ]

28:34.171 --> 28:36.131
Eh, funny story ‐‐ um...

28:36.131 --> 28:37.507
Oh, no.
She double‐booked.

28:37.507 --> 28:39.885
You did not respond
to my text.

28:39.885 --> 28:42.512
Yes, I'm pretty sure
that I did.

28:42.512 --> 28:43.513
No.

28:43.513 --> 28:44.973
O‐Oh. No.
Mm‐hmm.

28:44.973 --> 28:47.768
Um...[ Clears throat ]
I guess I never hit "send."

28:47.768 --> 28:49.811
Right.
And then
you called me ‐‐

28:49.811 --> 28:51.939
your second option.

28:51.939 --> 28:54.733
No, it's okay.
Enough said.

28:54.733 --> 28:56.902
She's all yours.
N‐‐ Alonzo, wait, I ‐‐

28:56.902 --> 28:58.570
You know, I th‐‐
I think I'm gonna go, too.

28:58.570 --> 29:00.489
Really? We can't just s‐stay
and have some wine and ‐‐

29:00.489 --> 29:01.782
and ‐‐ and talk about it?

29:01.782 --> 29:03.200
No.

29:03.200 --> 29:05.202
I've ‐‐ I've acted like
I'm cool with being

29:05.202 --> 29:06.370
one of two guys
you're dating

29:06.370 --> 29:09.247
'cause I like you so much.

29:09.247 --> 29:11.416
Well, that and
I thought one day,

29:11.416 --> 29:13.168
you might actually
pick me.

29:13.168 --> 29:14.461
James, I ‐‐

29:14.461 --> 29:17.339
It's just ‐‐ It's a little hard
on the ego, so...

29:17.339 --> 29:19.174
[ Clears throat ]

29:19.174 --> 29:20.676
Enjoy the rest
of your night.

29:22.177 --> 29:24.763
By the way...

29:24.763 --> 29:26.598
you look amazing.

29:26.598 --> 29:30.852
♪♪

29:30.852 --> 29:33.480
Uh, that was brutal.

29:33.480 --> 29:36.525
[ Sighs ] I'm gonna go
invite her to sit with us.

29:36.525 --> 29:38.318
No, wait, wh‐‐
A‐Are you crazy?

29:38.318 --> 29:39.736
Let her go.
Pretend it didn't happen.

29:39.736 --> 29:41.154
♪♪

29:41.154 --> 29:42.114
Counselor.

29:44.032 --> 29:45.701
What a nice surprise.

29:45.701 --> 29:47.452
♪♪

29:47.452 --> 29:51.623
Yeah. Angela,
this is my client Elijah.

29:51.623 --> 29:55.127
And silent partner
in this fine establishment.

29:55.127 --> 29:56.920
Aren't the meatballs
to die for?

29:56.920 --> 29:58.714
They're great.

29:58.714 --> 30:00.007
Will you excuse me
for a minute?

30:00.007 --> 30:01.508
Of course.

30:01.508 --> 30:04.136
♪♪

30:04.136 --> 30:05.429
What the hell
are you doing?

30:05.429 --> 30:08.890
It is a crime
how easy it is...

30:08.890 --> 30:10.892
...to hack a baby monitor.

30:10.892 --> 30:15.313
♪♪

30:15.313 --> 30:18.150
You're making a mistake,
threatening us.

30:18.150 --> 30:20.444
I don't make threats.
I make promises.

30:20.444 --> 30:23.697
And I always follow through ‐‐
just like I expect you to.

30:23.697 --> 30:26.241
From this moment on,
whatever line

30:26.241 --> 30:28.201
I need you to cross,
you will cross it.

30:28.201 --> 30:29.286
Whoever I tell you
to represent,

30:29.286 --> 30:31.121
you'll take them on
as a client.

30:31.121 --> 30:33.540
And if I need you to betray
their interests in my benefit,

30:33.540 --> 30:34.666
you'll do it.

30:34.666 --> 30:36.543
I'll get disbarred.

30:36.543 --> 30:37.919
Well,
only if you get caught.

30:37.919 --> 30:40.922
This is what you agreed to trade
for your wife and child.

30:40.922 --> 30:43.675
♪♪

30:43.675 --> 30:47.345
And you do not want
to default on this debt.

30:47.345 --> 30:50.348
♪♪

30:50.348 --> 30:52.642
Oh, and you gotta order
the pot de crème.

30:54.519 --> 30:56.063
It's sinful.

30:56.063 --> 31:01.610
♪♪

31:01.610 --> 31:06.740
♪♪

31:09.993 --> 31:11.161
[ Indistinct chatter ]

31:11.161 --> 31:13.872
Chen.
Hmm?

31:13.872 --> 31:17.167
If you want the job,
all you gotta do is ask.

31:17.167 --> 31:20.003
What?
You sabotaged Webb.

31:20.003 --> 31:21.838
I don't know what
you're talking about.

31:21.838 --> 31:23.173
His cat personality?

31:23.173 --> 31:25.300
Well, that's got you
written all over it.

31:25.300 --> 31:27.260
Look, if you want me
to ride with you,

31:27.260 --> 31:28.512
you don't need
to make up an excuse.

31:28.512 --> 31:29.888
Just ask me.

31:31.014 --> 31:32.516
Sgt. Grey: Good morning.

31:32.516 --> 31:34.226
So, we have
a clearer understanding

31:34.226 --> 31:36.520
of yesterday's
sniper shooting.

31:36.520 --> 31:38.438
According to
the Gang Unit,

31:38.438 --> 31:40.941
the victim had a falling‐out
with Elijah Stone.

31:40.941 --> 31:42.359
So, it <i>was</i>
a contract killing?

31:42.359 --> 31:44.361
Looks like it.

31:44.361 --> 31:46.029
Gangs put together
a list of potential shooters

31:46.029 --> 31:47.614
that Elijah might use.

31:47.614 --> 31:50.450
We ran it against
military personnel records

31:50.450 --> 31:52.619
and came up with
a dozen names.

31:52.619 --> 31:54.996
And you guessed it ‐‐
detectives want patrol

31:54.996 --> 31:56.414
to do the initial canvass.

31:56.414 --> 31:59.417
So...let's get to work.

31:59.417 --> 32:01.545
Oh, oh.
One more thing.

32:01.545 --> 32:03.296
Sergeant?

32:03.296 --> 32:06.258
Yeah, um, I've decided
to spread the love

32:06.258 --> 32:10.011
and give someone else a chance
to be my go‐fer today.

32:11.888 --> 32:13.890
Smitty, you're up.

32:13.890 --> 32:15.392
Seriously?

32:15.392 --> 32:16.935
I'm sorry, you have something
to add, Officer Chen?

32:16.935 --> 32:18.520
[ Chuckles ] No.

32:18.520 --> 32:20.021
Sir.

32:20.021 --> 32:22.065
All right, that's it.

32:22.065 --> 32:23.316
Be safe out there.

32:23.316 --> 32:25.569
[ Indistinct chatter ]

32:25.569 --> 32:26.528
Sarge.

32:28.113 --> 32:30.282
The job doesn't require
any heavy lifting, right?

32:30.282 --> 32:32.284
I've got a tricky back.

32:32.284 --> 32:34.452
No. No lifting required.

32:34.452 --> 32:36.121
Including the
war bags, right?

32:36.121 --> 32:37.622
Yeah, Smitty,
I'll get the bags.

32:37.622 --> 32:38.874
[ Sighs ]

32:38.874 --> 32:41.168
♪♪

32:41.168 --> 32:42.377
How was the restaurant?

32:43.628 --> 32:44.796
What happened?

32:44.796 --> 32:45.964
They both showed up.

32:45.964 --> 32:48.884
Oh, no.
Oh, yes.

32:48.884 --> 32:50.844
Yesterday, I was dating
two cute guys,

32:50.844 --> 32:53.054
and today, zero.

32:54.347 --> 32:56.600
Well, it had to end
at some point, right?

32:56.600 --> 32:58.059
I mean, if you cared
about one of them,

32:58.059 --> 33:00.770
you would have made
a decision a while ago.

33:00.770 --> 33:02.480
I liked the freedom.

33:02.480 --> 33:05.984
It was fun being able
to take it slow.

33:05.984 --> 33:07.027
But?

33:09.070 --> 33:11.364
But I just ‐‐
I can't get the look

33:11.364 --> 33:13.325
on James' face
out of my head.

33:18.580 --> 33:20.832
And who's
our next contestant?

33:20.832 --> 33:22.292
Aiden Merritt, 32.

33:22.292 --> 33:23.501
One tour in Afghanistan,

33:23.501 --> 33:25.837
followed by six years
as a private contractor.

33:25.837 --> 33:27.255
Any priors?

33:27.255 --> 33:28.924
A couple domestic
complaints in Houston ‐‐

33:28.924 --> 33:29.841
an ex‐girlfriend ‐‐
but nothing since

33:29.841 --> 33:31.384
he moved to L. A.

33:31.384 --> 33:32.385
[ Door opens ]

33:32.385 --> 33:34.638
Hey.
Aiden Merritt?

33:34.638 --> 33:36.348
Yeah, that's me.

33:36.348 --> 33:38.183
What were you doing
yesterday at noon?

33:38.183 --> 33:40.185
[ Chuckles ]
That's an ominous question.

33:40.185 --> 33:42.854
Um, why do you
want to know?

33:42.854 --> 33:44.564
There was a sniper
shooting yesterday.
Oh, yeah, yeah.

33:44.564 --> 33:46.274
No, I did see that
on the news.

33:46.274 --> 33:48.777
And because of
my background, uh, yeah,

33:48.777 --> 33:50.153
I get why
you want to see me.

33:50.153 --> 33:51.446
The answer
to your question

33:51.446 --> 33:53.031
actually has some
irony to it, though,

33:53.031 --> 33:54.157
because yesterday afternoon,

33:54.157 --> 33:56.576
I was actually at
the Gun Club downtown.

33:56.576 --> 33:58.411
Well, that's good news.
You got any proof of that?

33:58.411 --> 34:00.330
Um...I might, uh ‐‐

34:00.330 --> 34:03.458
I might still have a receipt
for some ammo I bought.

34:03.458 --> 34:04.709
I could go look.

34:04.709 --> 34:07.128
Lucy: Mind if we
step inside?

34:07.128 --> 34:08.922
Uh, yeah.
Yeah, I do.

34:08.922 --> 34:10.257
But I'll be right back out.

34:10.257 --> 34:14.928
♪♪

34:14.928 --> 34:16.221
[ Door closes ]
I am getting a vibe.

34:16.221 --> 34:19.099
You getting a vibe?
Big‐time vibe.

34:19.099 --> 34:20.725
Smart about that
alibi, though.

34:20.725 --> 34:22.978
Gives him a reason
to be in the vicinity.

34:22.978 --> 34:25.897
♪♪

34:25.897 --> 34:27.816
Lucy, I'm looking
at a rifle.

34:27.816 --> 34:29.818
Then that gives us
probable cause.
[ Gun cocks ]

34:29.818 --> 34:34.155
♪♪

34:34.155 --> 34:35.573
I told you
to wait outside.

34:35.573 --> 34:39.202
Sir, I'm gonna need you
to show us your hands.

34:39.202 --> 34:40.453
Come on, man.
This is a mistake.

34:40.453 --> 34:41.538
I got the receipt
right here.

34:41.538 --> 34:42.956
Lucy: Yes, sir,
and we will get to that,

34:42.956 --> 34:44.291
but right now,
my partner asked you

34:44.291 --> 34:45.583
to show us your hands.

34:45.583 --> 34:47.127
[ Scoffs ]

34:47.127 --> 34:48.962
You really don't want me
to do that.

34:48.962 --> 34:50.964
Yes, we do.
Nice and slow.

34:52.173 --> 34:53.550
Okay.

34:53.550 --> 34:57.679
♪♪

34:57.679 --> 34:59.556
I already pulled the pin
in the bedroom.

34:59.556 --> 35:00.765
I was planning
to frag your car

35:00.765 --> 35:02.225
when you got back in,

35:02.225 --> 35:03.893
split town before
the smoke cleared.

35:03.893 --> 35:05.770
But...yeah.

35:05.770 --> 35:07.981
[ Sighs ]
Now you've forced the issue.

35:07.981 --> 35:10.483
You didn't survive a tour
just to die like this.

35:10.483 --> 35:12.402
It's better than going
to prison.

35:12.402 --> 35:15.488
Now, put down your guns,

35:15.488 --> 35:17.741
or we can all learn
what shrapnel tastes like.

35:17.741 --> 35:20.952
♪♪

35:20.952 --> 35:23.204
Okay.

35:23.204 --> 35:25.165
Fine. You win.
What are you doing?

35:25.165 --> 35:26.249
You're a better shot
than me.

35:26.249 --> 35:27.292
But I'm a little quicker
on my feet.

35:27.292 --> 35:28.543
Nolan.

35:28.543 --> 35:29.628
You got a better plan?

35:29.628 --> 35:31.546
What the hell are you two
talking about?

35:31.546 --> 35:32.922
The fuse on a grenade

35:32.922 --> 35:34.716
takes approximately
four seconds to detonate.

35:34.716 --> 35:36.593
He thinks if I shoot you
in the medulla,

35:36.593 --> 35:38.345
he'll have enough time
to grab the grenade

35:38.345 --> 35:39.721
after you drop it
and throw it outside

35:39.721 --> 35:40.847
before it explodes.

35:40.847 --> 35:42.349
Nolan ‐‐
Actually,
I was planning on

35:42.349 --> 35:43.767
kicking it back
into the house.

35:43.767 --> 35:45.852
Where he probably has
more grenades?

35:45.852 --> 35:47.562
♪♪

35:47.562 --> 35:48.938
You're right.
Change of plan.

35:48.938 --> 35:55.362
♪♪

35:55.362 --> 36:01.868
♪♪

36:01.868 --> 36:04.204
[ Electricity whirs ]

36:04.204 --> 36:05.622
[ Taser crackles ]

36:05.622 --> 36:08.917
♪♪

36:08.917 --> 36:10.001
Spoon's still attached.

36:10.001 --> 36:12.212
We're good.
Thank you.

36:12.212 --> 36:13.213
What? It worked.

36:14.506 --> 36:16.383
7‐Adam‐15.

36:16.383 --> 36:17.467
Requesting backup
and a supervisor

36:17.467 --> 36:18.677
on our location.

36:18.677 --> 36:20.845
[ Both panting ]
And the bomb squad.

36:20.845 --> 36:22.514
Please, can you take that
outside while we wait?

36:22.514 --> 36:23.765
That's right.
7‐Adam‐15.

36:23.765 --> 36:25.016
We're also gonna need
a bomb squad.

36:26.267 --> 36:28.061
[ Cellphone ringing, buzzing ]

36:29.562 --> 36:30.980
Hello?

36:30.980 --> 36:32.941
Where the hell
are all the baby monitors?

36:32.941 --> 36:36.111
Um...I threw them out.

36:36.111 --> 36:37.487
What? Why?

36:37.487 --> 36:39.531
<i>There was a ‐‐</i>
<i>a safety recall.</i>

36:39.531 --> 36:40.657
<i>Fire hazard.</i>

36:40.657 --> 36:42.075
We can get new ones.

36:42.075 --> 36:43.284
Higher tech.

36:43.284 --> 36:45.328
Okay. Good catch.
[ Chuckles ]

36:45.328 --> 36:46.329
[ Door opens ]

36:46.329 --> 36:47.831
♪♪

36:47.831 --> 36:49.040
Babe, I gotta go.

36:50.083 --> 36:51.710
Secretary wasn't
at her desk,

36:51.710 --> 36:54.546
so I figured
I'd just pop in.

36:54.546 --> 36:56.840
Yeah, sure.

36:56.840 --> 36:58.341
What can I do for you?

36:58.341 --> 37:00.468
I'm loving this
new attitude, Counselor.

37:00.468 --> 37:01.761
It's just the right balance

37:01.761 --> 37:04.764
between confidence
and obsequiousness.

37:04.764 --> 37:06.641
♪♪

37:06.641 --> 37:09.602
I need you to deliver this
to your new client.

37:09.602 --> 37:12.313
♪♪

37:12.313 --> 37:13.523
What new client?

37:13.523 --> 37:20.530
♪♪

37:20.530 --> 37:27.537
♪♪

37:27.537 --> 37:28.955
[ Sighs ]

37:28.955 --> 37:32.500
♪♪

37:32.500 --> 37:34.002
I'm Wesley Evers.

37:34.002 --> 37:35.879
I'll be representing you.
It's about friggin' time.

37:39.132 --> 37:40.633
Aiden:
Give it to me straight.

37:40.633 --> 37:42.385
How screwed am I?

37:42.385 --> 37:43.762
[ Sighs ]

37:43.762 --> 37:45.013
Well, we'll get to that.

37:46.765 --> 37:48.183
First, I have
something for you.

37:50.059 --> 37:52.312
Ah.
[ Chuckles ]

37:52.312 --> 37:53.605
He hesitates.

37:53.605 --> 37:56.191
You must be new to working
with our friend.

37:56.191 --> 37:57.275
Still in that phase

37:57.275 --> 37:59.194
where you think
you have free will.

37:59.194 --> 38:01.404
Let me guess ‐‐
you took an oath

38:01.404 --> 38:03.823
to uphold the law,
not break it,

38:03.823 --> 38:05.283
so now you're torn.

38:05.283 --> 38:07.577
Do you possibly
aid and abet a crime

38:07.577 --> 38:09.871
by giving me whatever's
in that envelope?

38:09.871 --> 38:12.457
I mean, the very act
of passing it to me

38:12.457 --> 38:13.958
is a likely
ethics violation,

38:13.958 --> 38:16.544
which could
get you disbarred.

38:16.544 --> 38:19.672
And yet...
you wouldn't be here

38:19.672 --> 38:21.132
if you had a choice,
would you?

38:37.482 --> 38:39.192
Actually, it's for you.

38:46.157 --> 38:48.952
[ Scoffs ]
You're lucky.

38:48.952 --> 38:52.580
Fail one of Elijah's tests,
you end up as fertilizer.

38:52.580 --> 38:55.500
So, how do you plan
to get me out of this mess?

38:55.500 --> 38:58.962
♪♪

38:58.962 --> 39:03.508
[ Indistinct chatter ]

39:03.508 --> 39:08.680
♪♪

39:08.680 --> 39:11.683
How's it going, Sarge?

39:11.683 --> 39:14.352
Fine. [ Sighs ]

39:14.352 --> 39:16.646
How come Smitty's
not doing the paperwork?

39:16.646 --> 39:19.232
♪♪

39:19.232 --> 39:20.817
He claims to be
allergic to paper.

39:20.817 --> 39:21.776
Hmm. [ Chuckles ]

39:21.776 --> 39:23.361
It's not funny.

39:23.361 --> 39:25.822
You should have
just asked me.

39:25.822 --> 39:27.866
I was doing you a favor.

39:27.866 --> 39:31.035
Yeah? How? By telling
the entire station
that you would rather

39:31.035 --> 39:33.663
ride with Smitty than me,
your old boot?

39:33.663 --> 39:37.292
Look, some would see it
as a demotion for you.

39:37.292 --> 39:38.918
You're back with
your training officer.

39:38.918 --> 39:41.963
Others might read...
[ Inhales deeply ]

39:41.963 --> 39:42.755
...something else into it.

39:42.755 --> 39:44.340
W‐Why?

39:44.340 --> 39:46.843
Because I'm a girl
and you're a boy?

39:46.843 --> 39:48.177
A very handsome boy.

39:48.177 --> 39:49.512
Oh, gag.

39:49.512 --> 39:52.265
Look, I really appreciate
the intention,

39:52.265 --> 39:54.434
but screw what
anyone else thinks.

39:54.434 --> 39:56.477
Being a sergeant's aide
would ‐‐

39:56.477 --> 39:57.228
Go‐fer.

39:58.479 --> 40:01.190
<i>...aide</i> would
make me stand out

40:01.190 --> 40:02.525
come promotion time.

40:02.525 --> 40:05.278
That alone makes it worth
putting up with your Tim tests

40:05.278 --> 40:08.364
and old‐school
code of honor again.

40:10.909 --> 40:13.202
So, are you saying
you want the job?

40:13.202 --> 40:15.538
If you're saying
you want me to do it.

40:15.538 --> 40:19.626
♪♪

40:19.626 --> 40:21.794
What the hell.
Let's do it.

40:21.794 --> 40:23.588
You get here an hour
before roll call tomorrow

40:23.588 --> 40:25.924
and I'll get you up to speed
on all the new protocols.

40:25.924 --> 40:27.133
Will do.

40:28.343 --> 40:29.719
Thank you.

40:29.719 --> 40:30.845
You're welcome.

40:30.845 --> 40:32.639
Good luck
with your paperwork.

40:32.639 --> 40:36.809
♪♪

40:36.809 --> 40:38.186
James. [ Scoffs ]

40:40.563 --> 40:42.273
What are you
doing here?

40:42.273 --> 40:44.317
Well, Aaron asked me
to come by,

40:44.317 --> 40:45.860
said he needed
to talk to me.

40:45.860 --> 40:47.195
That was a lie.

40:47.195 --> 40:48.529
I'm straight‐up
playing matchmaker.

40:48.529 --> 40:49.822
Boot, I'm ‐‐
Hold ‐‐ Hold on.

40:49.822 --> 40:51.282
I'm just trying
to do what I can

40:51.282 --> 40:52.492
to fix the mess
that I caused.

40:52.492 --> 40:54.452
You were kind to me
yesterday when we met,

40:54.452 --> 40:56.996
so I feel compelled
to return the favor.

40:56.996 --> 40:59.290
The second that I offered
Detective Harper

40:59.290 --> 41:01.960
my reservation,
she invited you.

41:01.960 --> 41:04.128
And when
you didn't respond,

41:04.128 --> 41:05.880
she was gonna go alone.

41:05.880 --> 41:08.466
But I pushed her
to invite the other guy.

41:08.466 --> 41:10.343
♪♪

41:10.343 --> 41:12.345
You know how close to the vest
she plays things.

41:12.345 --> 41:14.555
I could still see
how upset she was

41:14.555 --> 41:15.848
when she saw that
she hurt you.

41:15.848 --> 41:18.434
So, maybe...

41:18.434 --> 41:20.937
I don't know,
give her a second chance.

41:20.937 --> 41:22.355
I'll see you tomorrow.

41:22.355 --> 41:27.735
♪♪

41:27.735 --> 41:30.071
That all true?

41:30.071 --> 41:31.406
Yeah.

41:31.406 --> 41:33.741
♪♪

41:33.741 --> 41:36.536
I'm sorry
I messed everything up.

41:36.536 --> 41:38.079
[ Chuckles ]

41:40.832 --> 41:42.208
Okay.
[ Clears throat ]

41:44.085 --> 41:46.004
You can take me
to dinner.

41:46.004 --> 41:47.630
I can?
Yes, you can.

41:47.630 --> 41:49.215
Okay.

41:49.215 --> 41:52.802
But if there's anything on
the menu that I need to Google

41:52.802 --> 41:55.388
to figure out what it is,
I'm walking.

41:55.388 --> 41:57.849
No, you're not
having that.
I'm ‐‐ I'm just ‐‐
I'm ‐‐ I'm not ‐‐

41:57.849 --> 41:59.517
Can't do that.
Refuse. Refuse.
Okay, I‐I think
I got it.

41:59.517 --> 42:02.270
I've been thinking about
your arson case.

42:02.270 --> 42:04.147
You kill someone,
you set a fire to cover it up.

42:04.147 --> 42:05.732
Pretty standard move.

42:05.732 --> 42:08.776
What's strange
is the broken bones.

42:08.776 --> 42:11.946
So I ran a search and found
two recent unsolved cases

42:11.946 --> 42:13.364
with similar MO's.

42:13.364 --> 42:14.657
Both in Nevada,

42:14.657 --> 42:17.285
both suffered broken legs
before dying in a fire.

42:17.285 --> 42:20.204
Three murders with
the same twisted MO.

42:20.204 --> 42:21.956
We've got a serial killer
on our hands.

42:21.956 --> 42:23.124
♪♪

42:29.172 --> 42:37.597
♪♪

42:37.597 --> 42:46.314
♪♪

42:46.314 --> 42:54.197
♪♪
